CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 21, 1963, pg. 3 reads: "Death Scene - The station wagon driven by James Smith of Mahon St., in hot pursuit of another car, was engulfed in flames which claimed the lives of Smith and two others, on Saturday, when the station wagon, after striking another car, his the bridge curb area shown above. - Harris Photo.image published by Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, with graphic addition of arrow.
TitMainTitle: 31st Street Bridge, site of fatal car accident, with sidewalks and street lights, hillside with trees and houses in distance
